approved: true
description: <p>I created the NovaCut font about \
  14-15 years ago for making inscriptions on stone. \
  Initially the font contained only capitals \
  and digits and existed only on paper and stone \
  inscriptions. In 2010 I decided transfer this \
  font to a computer, and made the missing lowercase \
  and some basical signs; it was initially named \
  Gothica.</p> \
  <p>By the way I made other versions of some \
  letters. It was a lot of this at the \
  end of my work. I decided create new fonts \
  based on these letters. And finally I created \
  six fonts family and named these fonts Nova \
  (NovaCut, NovaFlat, NovaOval, NovaRound, \
  NovaSlim, NovaSquare - by the shape of \
  individual fonts). At last I created monospace \
  font - NovaMono - the seventh part of \
  this family.</p>

